# tmux notes
#

session -> windows -> panes

### pane control
Ctrl+b % : vertical split pane 
Ctrl+b " : horizontal split pane
Ctrl+b o : switch to next pane
Ctrl+b q : show pane name/number, type number and goto that pane
Ctrl+b x : kill current pane.
Ctrl+b ! : pane become window
Ctrl+b z : pane zoom out / zoom in.

### windows control
Ctrl+b c : create window
Ctrl+b w : switch / select window
Ctrl+b n : switch next window 
Ctrl+b p : switch previous window
Ctrl+b <number> : switch to select <number> window
Ctrl+b & : kill current window
Ctrl+b , : rename window

### session control
Ctrl+b $ : rename session
Ctrl+b d : detach session / means background
Ctrl+b s : select session
Ctrl+b ( : previous session
Ctrl=B ) : next session


#### list session
tmux ls 
#### kill session
tmux kill-session -t target-session-number
#### kill all session but the current session
tmux kill-session -a

